The paper discusses a platform for applying supervised machine learning to data, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The recommendation engine component of the platform involves selecting and running optimal algorithm configurations for various datasets, which could fall under information retrieval (cs.IR) or artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The platform also involves downloading reproducible code and fitted models, which could fall under databases (cs.DB). Finally, the paper discusses benchmarking different recommendation strategies, which could fall under cybernetics (cs.CY).
